    "CONTENT": {
        "Career": "On 9 May 2022, SC Freiburg announced that after six seasons with the club, Haberer would sign with Union Berlin for the 2022–23 Bundesliga season. On 16 October 2022, he scored his first Bundesliga brace in a 2–0 win for Union Berlin against Borussia Dortmund. On the final matchday of the 2023–24 season, he netted a stoppage-time goal in a 2–1 win over his former club SC Freiburg, securing Union's continued presence in the Bundesliga.",
